other_tests.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated to 1.0 cm, with trace periappendiceal stranding. A hyperdensity near the base of the appendix could represent an appendicolith. The visualized lung fields are within normal limits. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum are all within normal limits. There is no evidence of retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
